# Canonical W2C (Pbcn, mp-2034) CIF for the catalysis toolkit.
#
# Provenance:
#   - Source:    Materials Project mp-2034
#   - Recipe:    pymatgen Structure.from_dict(MP_doc['structure'])
#                -> CifWriter(struct, symprec=0.01)
#   - Audit:     CLAUDE OUTPUTS/Catalysis-Toolkit/Catalysis-Toolkit_CIF-Audit_v1.md
#   - Generated: 2026-05-01
#
# Why this is the canonical CIF:
#   GSAS-II imports this as Pbcn (SG 60) with 2 atoms in the asymmetric
#   unit and 8 symmetry operators. After symmetry expansion it gives
#   12 atoms, matching the conventional Pbcn cell of W2C.
#
#   The CIF reduces the cell to 3 free cell parameters (a, b, c with
#   alpha=beta=gamma=90 enforced) and 4 free fractional coordinates
#   (1 W asym site + 1 C asym site, each with 1 free Wyckoff parameter).
#   A P1 import of the same structure would give GSAS-II 6 cell DoF +
#   36 XYZ DoF, which diverges with broad nanocrystalline peaks.
#
#   Variants B, C, and D from the audit are byte-identical and all reduce
#   to this CIF. Variant A (P1, 12 explicit atoms) is what the retired
#   mp_w2c_pbcn_compat policy used to ship; do not use it.
#
# DO NOT EDIT BY HAND. To regenerate, see fetch_w2c_audit_cifs.py.

data_W2C
_symmetry_space_group_name_H-M   Pbcn
_cell_length_a   4.75632200
_cell_length_b   6.11103400
_cell_length_c   5.23726500
_cell_angle_alpha   90.00000000
_cell_angle_beta   90.00000000
_cell_angle_gamma   90.00000000
_symmetry_Int_Tables_number   60
_chemical_formula_structural   W2C
_chemical_formula_sum   'W8 C4'
_cell_volume   152.22658256
_cell_formula_units_Z   4
loop_
 _symmetry_equiv_pos_site_id
 _symmetry_equiv_pos_as_xyz
